JENKINS  --> Jenkins is an open-source automation server used to automate parts of the software development process, especially building, testing, and deploying code.
SETUP-
		1.install java 			--yum install java17 -y #if u want specific java version --yum whatprovides java
		2.download jenkins from web	--sudo weget -0 url
		3.download dependences		--sudo rpm url
		4.upgrade and install      	--yum upgrade & yum install jenkins -y
		5.enable and restart 		--systemctl enable jenkins & systemctl start jenkins & for status use systemctl jenkins status 
		6.set port number as 8080 in the aws or use command line like --java -jar jenkins.war --httpPort=9090
		7.copy the ip and add :8080 like ---192.32.22:8080 and paste in web browser 
		8.open jenkins and ask use name and password and its show the path for password so from that path we can get password for jenkins 

STEPS TO MAKE CONNECTIONS B/W GITHUB - GITHUB 
    Requirments -Install jenkins and running state
                Install github and create a public repo 
    1.Install plugins for github and git 
        *Go to Manage Jenkins > Manage Plugins
            -->github integration
            -->git
    2.Config Github Credentials in jenkins
       *1st go to github create github credentials 
         in github      -->gituhb profile settings > developer settings > personals access tokens > token (classic) > Generate new token (classic) >copy & save the token
         in jenkins     -->After that go to Manage Jenkins > Manage Credentials > (global) 
                        -->then fill Kind,ID and Secret (Paste GitHub_Token)
    3.Configure Source Code Management
        -->go to configuration > select the Git in source_code_mangement > give github_url and credentials > optional (origin,refspec)>save 

            OPTIONAL (#select this option only if you want to set auto trigger when any changes occur in github(after push))
        -->it asks build trigger option pick GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling 
           GITHUB  --> Go to your GitHub repository > Settings > Webhooks
                     Add webhook
                    Payload URL: http://<your-jenkins-server>/github-webhook/
                    Replace <your-jenkins-server> with your Jenkins serverâ€™s public URL
                    Content type: application/json
                    Secret: (optional, but recommended for security)
                    Events: Select Just the push event or Let me select individual events (e.g., Pushes and Pull Requests)
                    Ensure the webhook is Active
                    Click Add webhook
            jenkins -->Save and Test the Integration
                        Save your Jenkins job configuration
                        Make a change in your GitHub repository and push it
                        Jenkins should automatically trigger a build
    4.save and apply and then click manually build_with_parameters and its build the project 

BUILD_TRIGGER_OPTIONS
1.Trigger builds remotely (eg:from scripts)
2.Build after other build builds
3.Build periodicaly
4.Github hook for trigger GITSCM polling 
5.poll SCM



        




            
            




    
